$ ctria3_free_thermal.bdf
$ Two CTRIA3 forming a 1 m × 1 m square — free thermal expansion
$
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      minimal in-plane set (all compatible with u=alpha*dT*x, v=alpha*dT*y):
$             fix T1+T2 of node 1, fix T2 of node 2, fix T1 of node 4
$           out-of-plane stability:
$             fix T3 of nodes 1, 2, 4 (non-collinear, compatible with w=0 for z=0 plate)
$
$ Expected (alpha*dT = 1e-3):
$   node 2 at (1,0): u = 1e-3 m
$   node 3 at (1,1): u = 1e-3 m, v = 1e-3 m
$   node 4 at (0,1): v = 1e-3 m
$   Stress ≈ 0 in both triangles
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTRIA3 FREE THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
CTRIA3,1,1,1,2,3
CTRIA3,2,1,1,3,4
$ In-plane minimal BCs (compatible with free-expansion field)
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
SPC1,1,1,4
$ Out-of-plane: fix T3, R1, R2 (DOFs 3,4,5) of all nodes.
$ Thermal expansion is purely in-plane; bending DOFs are zero by symmetry.
SPC1,1,345,1
SPC1,1,345,2
SPC1,1,345,3
SPC1,1,345,4
$ Uniform temperature
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
ENDDATA
